This paper deals with consensus protocols for multi-agent systems, which is a topic in the field of control theory and systems engineering. Therefore, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves mathematical analysis of the convergence rate, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the use of noise-attenuation gains and the study of their effects on consensus could place the paper in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
